<TITLE> Absent Marica and Niculae add to Romanian injury woes </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 BUCHAREST, Sept 9 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Romania added Ciprian Marica and Daniel Niculae to their growing injury list on Monday after both forwards were ruled out of Wednesday's World Cup qualifying trip to the Faroe Islands. Romania, already missing Adrian Mutu, Cristian Chivu, Razvan Rat, Ovidiu Petre and Banel Nicolita through injury, were surprisingly beaten 3-0 by Lithuania in their Group Seven opener on Saturday. "Marica was strongly hit in his right thigh against Lithuania, while Niculae has strained a right leg muscle," national team spokesman Paul Zaharia told Reuters. "Both remained in Bucharest to nurse their injuries" Defender Gabriel Tamas is also doubtful for the match through injury, Zaharia said, adding that no replacements had been called up for VfB Stuttgart's Marica and Niculae of French side Auxerre. Romanian Soccer Federation president Mircea Sandu warned coach Victor Piturca on Sunday that his position would be discussed after Wednesday's game in Torshavn
